rComments: Brilliant professor and very modern teaching style.  She takes historical events/objects and makes them relevant to present day.  She's not about dates, but about historical context and meaning.  Be prepared to do some work if you want a high grade, you get only what you work for in her classes.
The class is absolutely terrible. I dread coming to class because it's so boring, unimportant, and hard. Not Recommended.

Her quizzes and exams were very specific and most of the questions related to the readings (which is usually 30 pages a week). Her grading was also difficult and hard to get an A. I usually dreaded going to class because the lectures were dull.  But she was nice and helpful during office hours.

Extremely difficult! She makes the class seem a lot harder then it should and her time limits for finishing work is not realistic at all. Readings are difficult to understand and boring. She's also a very harsh grader. Wouldn't recommend

Horrible; READS off paper for lectures, not putting any notes online or having a PowerPoint. Her quizzes are VERY specific; even if you read the articles you still fail. Its hard to do well on the essay exams because the only notes provided are the ones you jot down when she talks SUPER FAST; therefore we have incomplete information for the exam.
Great prof, provides a variety of interesting readings and conducts discussions well. Killer fashion sense.
